Background

Measure Definitions

See here for risk model performance measure definitions.

Target Performance Measures

We consider estimation of:

  1. the performance of the fitted risk model
  2. the performance of the working risk model

under both correctly specified and mis-specified models.

Confidence Interval Calculations

See here for details regarding confidence interval calculations.

Model

We simulate data from a logistic model with linear terms: \(Risk(X) = Pr(D=1 | X) = expit(\beta X)\) so that our fitted model is correctly specified.

Cases

case n marginal odds ratio no. markers
1 250 1.25 1
2 500 1.25 1
3 250 2 1
4 250 1.25 4
5 250 1.25 10

Setup 2: incorrectly specified models

True model: \(logit(P(D=1|X)) = \beta_0 + \beta_1 X + \frac{\beta_1}{10} X^2\) (for a single marker) However, we fit a logistic model with only linear terms. \(\beta s\) are chosen so that the marginal odds ratio for each marker is 1.25 for weak markers and 2 for strong.
